<1ST_LINE>u p PM-Politics-Quotes     09-17 0272</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Politics-Quotes,260</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Friday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, mocking Dukakis for trying to show his national
security prowess by riding in a tank: ``The tank did not fit. You
cannot fool the Soviet leadership by knocking America's defense for
10 years and then riding around in a tank for 10 minutes.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, criticizing Bush's lack of leadership in the
war against drugs: ``George Bush was supposed to be in charge of
that war, and we all know what happened ... You know, if you don't
show up at school, you fail, and if you don't show up at your job
as chief officer of the war on drugs, you fail, the American people
lose, and the drug lords take over.''
   
   LLOYD BENTSEN, saying that Bush has failed to speak out against
questionable Reagan administration policies and: ``When George Bush
speaks out against Mike Dukakis. We should all remember that when
it came to speaking out against arms to Iran, when it came to
speaking out against cozy deals with Gen. (Manuel Antonio) Noriega
of Panama, when it came to speaking out against economic policies
that have almost tripled the national debt, George Bush didn't
speak, he just voted present.''
   
   DAN QUAYLE, chiding Dukakis for waffling on defense issues, and
harkening back to the Massachusetts governor's earlier suggestion
that farmers solve their economic woes by growing Belgian endive:
``I decided to sum it up this way: His farm policy is the Belgian
endive and his defense policy is the Belgian waffle.''
</TEXT>
