<HEAD>Worldwide Nudists Group Gathers In Yugoslavia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wondering what to wear isn't a worry
for one group of conventioneers in the northern Adriatic resort of
Rovinj, where nudists from 21 nations kicked off their annual
congress on Saturday.
   About 500 delegates from the International Naturists Federation
met in the resort town on the Istrian peninsula for the three-day
gathering, the news agency Tanjug reported.
   Delegates are from throughout Europe, the United States and
Canada, it said.
   Among the agenda items is a round-table discussion on
``Naturism, Tourism and Leisure Time,'' the Tanjug said.
   This is the second time Yugoslavia has hosted an international
nudist meeting. In 1972 the European naturist center of Koversada
hosted the 13th world congress of nudists.
